segments.text:
Arjuna, the one who neither hates illumination, activity, or confusion when they arise, nor longs for them when they are absent;

who sits as if indifferent, not disturbed by the qualities; who thinks "the qualities are doing their work" and stands firm, unmoved;

the same in pleasure and pain, self-contained, treating a clod, stone, and gold the same; treating the liked and disliked the same, steady, the same in praise and blame of himself;

the same in honor and dishonor, the same toward friend and foe, giving up all undertakings — that person has gone beyond the qualities.

Whoever serves me with the unswerving yoga of devotion — going beyond the qualities, becomes fit to become Brahman.

For I am the foundation of Brahman — immortal, imperishable, of eternal dharma, and of absolute happiness.

